 Plague\">{{Cite web |url=http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |title=In Memory of the 1910 Harbin Plague |access-date=2011-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028165551/http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |archive-date=2017-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Patterson1\">{{Cite journal |last=Patterson |first=K. D. |last2=Pyle |first2=G. F. |year=1991 |title=The geography and mortality of the 1918 influenza pandemic |journal=Bulletin of the History of Medicine |volume=65 |issue=1 |pages=4\u201321 |pmid=2021692}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"1911e\">{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Plague |volume=21 |pages=693\u2013705}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"DSHS\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |title=Texas Department of State Health Services, History of Plague |access-date=2008-07-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HfryBSov?url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |archive-date=2013-06-26 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Faruque et al 2005\">{{Cite journal |last=Faruque |first=S. M. |last2=Islam |first2=M. J. |last3=Ahmad |first3=Q. S. |last4=Faruque |first4=A. S. G. |last5=Sack |first5=D. A. |last6=Nair |first6=G. B. |last7=Mekalanos |first7=J. J. |year=2005 |title=Self-limiting nature of seasonal cholera epidemics: Role of host-mediated amplification of phage |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences |volume=102 |issue=17 |pages=6119\u20136124 |bibcode=2005PNAS..102.6119F |doi=10.1073/pnas.0502069102 |pmc=1087956 |pmid=15829587}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"WHOint\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |title=World Health Organization action in Afghanistan aims to control debilitating leishmaniasis |access-date=16 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012030854/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |archive-date=12 October 2017 |url-status=li