ks==\n* {{Imdb title|id=0197270|title=Barefoot in Athens}}\n{{George Schaefer}}\n{{Socrates navbox}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Barefoot In Athens (Film)}}\n[[Category:1966 television films]]\n[[Category:American television films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Hallmark Hall of Fame episodes]]\n[[Category:1960s drama films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by George Schaefer]]\n[[Category:Films set in Athens]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 4th century BC]]\n[[Category:Films set in ancient Greece]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Socrates]]\n{{US-tv-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Barefoot in Athens\n| image          =\n| image size     =\n| caption        =\n| director       = [[George Schaefer (director)|George Schaefer]]\n| producer       = [[George Schaefer (director)|George Schaefer]]\n| writer         = [[Maxwell Anderson]]<br>(play)<br>Robert Husting<br>(adaptation)\n| narrator       =\n| starring       = [[Peter Ustinov]]\n| music          = Bernard Green\n| cinematography =\n| editing        =\n| distributor    =\n| released       = 1966\n| runtime        = 76 min.\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n| preceded by    =\n| followed by    =\n}}\n\n'''''Barefoot in Athens''''' is a 1966 [[Emmy Award]]-winning ''[[Hallmark Hall of Fame]]'' television movie, directed by [[George Schaefer (director)|George Schaefer]]. It stars [[Peter Ustinov]], [[Geraldine Page]], [[Anthony Quayle]], [[Lloyd Bochner]] and [[Christopher Walken]] in his film debut.\n\n==Plot==\nThe film concerns the trial and last days of [[Socrates]].\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Peter Ustinov]] as [[Socrates]]\n*[[Geraldine Page]] as [[Xantippe]]\n*[[Anthony Quayle]] as [[Pausanias (general)|King Pausanias of Sparta]]\n*[[Lloyd Bochner]] as [[Critias]]\n*[[Christopher Walken]] as [[Lamprocles]]\n*Eric Berry as Meletos\n*Frank Griso 